Done. Implemented the base tool and agent interfaces — here's a summary:

**`src/finroot/tools/base.py`** — `BaseTool(ABC, Generic[In, Out])` with:
- SHA-256 TTL cache (configurable `ttl_seconds`, default 300s)
- Token-bucket rate limiter (`rate_per_sec`, default 5.0)
- Retry with exponential backoff (`max_retries`=3, `base_delay`=1.0)
- Audit-trail emission (`tool.called` / `tool.failed`) on every call
- `ToolCallError` raised on failure — never silent, no synthetic data

**`src/finroot/agents/base.py`** — `BaseAgent(ABC)` with:
- Holds `LLMProvider`, `list[BaseTool]`, `AuditTrail`
- Abstract `act(state) -> state`
- `_call_tool(state, name, inp)` helper that dispatches to a named tool and records a `Citation`

**`tests/unit/test_base_interfaces.py`** — 14 tests covering cache hit/miss/expiry, rate limiting, loud failure propagation, audit emission on success/failure, agent dispatch, unknown tool rejection.

**Acceptance:** `ruff check` clean, all 14 pytest tests pass. Report written to `work/reports/wave-1/05-base-tool-agent-interfaces.report.md`.
